    "body": "> could you explain further why using the forked network's chain ID could be dangerous?\r\n\r\n@chanhosuh: You are signing txs that can be broadcasted to the forked network, accidentally or by an attacker. If you are sure this won't happen, or you are ok with that risk, you can explicitly set the same chainId.\r\n\r\nYou are right, this is now fixed, so I'm closing this issue.",
